text: Guadalupe Victoria Municipality is a municipality in the Mexican state of Puebla. According to the National Statistics Institute (INEGI), it had a population of 15,041 inhabitants in the 2005 census. Its total area is 239.83 km². It is named after Guadalupe Victoria, the first president of Mexico. Its geographical coordinates are 19° 17′ North, and 97° 20′ West. Its average altitude is above sea level. Its highest elevation is the rhyolitic twin dome volcano Las Derrumbadas (3480 m). ==External links== https://web.archive.org/web/20070324000550/http://www.e-local.gob.mx/work/templates/enciclo/puebla/Mpios/21067a.htm Category:Municipalities of Puebla
